getPosition

public long getPosition()
Returns the current position within this iterator. The number returned is the 0-based index of the next Row in the iterator, i.e. the one that will be returned on the subsequent next call.

Note that this method does not check if there is a next element, i.e. an empty iterator will always return 0.

Specified by:
getPosition in interface javax.jcr.RangeIterator
Returns:
the current position withing this iterator.
